        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Chemistry Insight\nThe positive E° of +0.34 V places copper below hydrogen in the activity series, meaning Cu metal does **not** dissolve in non-oxidizing acids (e.g., dilute HCl). This property, combined with copper's excellent electrical conductivity, underpins its widespread use in wiring and electronics — it remains stable under most ambient aqueous conditions.",
